<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-43-0432 </DOCNO><TEXT>In India rules and regulations for radiation safety cover the entire rangeof nuclear fuel cycle activities as well as the application of radiationsources in the country. Under the Atomic Energy Act of 1962, rules forradiation protection, waste management, etc., were promulgated. The AtomicEnergy Regulatory Board is the competent authority for the enforcementof these rules. The status of enforcement and the experience gained arediscussed in the paper.</TEXT></DOC>